          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was constructed of enriched Ni-60 > 99.8%",
                "electroplated up to a thickness of 1.2 mg/cm**2 on to",
                "a 250 mum gold backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma ray linear polarizations were measured at",
                "90 degrees to the beam direction using a three Ge(Li)",
                "Compton polarimeter.",
                "An escape-suppressed spectrometer was used to measure",
                "the angular distributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "2UK LVP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the Liverpool EN Tandem Van de Graaff",
                "accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The distribution intensities of the gamma rays were",
                "normalised with respect to a monitor gamma ray in the",
                "scatterer Ge(Li) detector of the polarimeter which was",
                "placed at 90 degree to the beam direction. Correction",
                "for the relative dead-time of the two detectors and",
                "their associated electronics was made using a pulser",
                "fed into the pre-amplifiers of both detectors and",
                "amounted to about 0.5%. A correction was also made for",
                "the absorption of low-energy gamma rays in the gold",
                "backing of the target and the maximum correction was",
                "15% for 200 keV and 5% for 400 keV gamma rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.The results of the analysis of singles",
                "angular distributions for spins, parities, Legendre",
                "coefficients (corrected for solid-angle effects),",
                "branching ratios, linear polarisations and the mixing",
                "ratios for the best fit to the data for all acceptable",
                "spin hypotheses are summarised in table 1."
              ]
            }
          ],
